Three people have been injured after a helicopter crashed at the Virginia Airport in Durban on Wednesday morning. Medi Response Search and Rescue unit as well as police search and rescue, Metro police SAR and others attended to the scene. According to Medi Response Search and Rescue spokesperson Paul Herbst, the pilot and the two passengers are understood to have suffered minor injuries and were transported to a nearby hospital for further care. “The cause of the crash is unknown and will be investigated by the Civil Aviation Authority,” said Herbst. 